# CITING INSTRUCTIONS

Always cite the source of your information by including its ID in brackets directly after the relevant sentence, for example: [source:abc123] or [note:xyz456].

- Use IDs exactly as provided — never invent or modify them.
- The ID includes its type prefix: "source:...", "note:...", "insight:...". Always use the full ID.
